L'Oréal S.A. is a French personal care company headquartered in Clichy, Hauts-de-Seine with a registered office in Paris. It is the world's largest cosmetics company and has developed activities in the field concentrating on hair colour, skin care, sun protection, make-up, perfume, and hair care.Upon the death of her mother, Liliane Bettencourt, who was principal shareholder, as of 2020 Françoise Bettencourt Meyers is the owner of the company, with a 33.14% stake.